rComments: Amazing Prof. He was actually passionate about what he taught and would always help anyone that needed help. The test, exam, and assignments were extremely fair. The course itself is also very interesting. There is no textbook but he makes his own notes which is like a packet of 20 each class (kind of his own textbook).

Professor Vyas can seem very intimidating at the beginning, but don't you worry, the moment he starts talking, you'll know what an amazing person he is. His lectures are a bit heavy, but he hands out very detailed notes that work as a substitute to the textbook in most cases. He can also be very funny, caring, and helpful when you need his help.
